Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 450 degrees, distributing racks evenly. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges (like steak fries).

Spread out @Panko Breadcrumbs{1%cup} on a #baking sheet{}. Toast in oven until golden brown, ~{2-3%minutes}. Transfer to a #large bowl{} or #shallow dish{}, then stir in @Parmesan Cheese{1/2%cup} and a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1-2%tbsp}. Season with @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Toss potatoes, a large drizzle of olive oil, @Dried Rosemary{1%teaspoon}, and a large pinch of salt and pepper on baking sheet used for panko. Roast in oven until nicely browned and crisp, ~{25-30%minutes}, flipping halfway through.

Cut @Chicken Breasts{24%ounce} into 1-inch-wide strips. Season all over with salt and pepper. Crack @Eggs{2} into a #medium bowl{} and lightly beat. Working one piece at a time, dip chicken into eggs, letting excess drip off, then coat in crust mixture, pressing to adhere. Place on a lightly oiled baking sheet.

Toss @Green Beans{12%ounce} on a third baking sheet with a drizzle of olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper. Bake green beans and chicken in oven until chicken is no longer pink in center and green beans are tender and slightly crisp at the edges, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> Alternatively, cook the green beans with a drizzle of olive oil in a large pan over medium heat until tender, 4-5 minutes, then season with salt and pepper.

Stir together @Honey{3%ounce} and @Dijon Mustard{1/4%cup} in a #small bowl{}. Give sauce a taste and add more mustard 1 tsp at a time until you reach desired balance of spicy and sweet. Divide chicken, potatoes, and green beans between plates. Serve with honey mustard sauce on the side for dipping.